Since JDK 17, Random and SecureRandom implement the interface RandomGenerator which has a new method [`nextGaussian(double mean, double stddev)`](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/util/random/RandomGenerator.html#nextGaussian(double,double))

OpenJDK Implementation is same as in previous answers:

```java
        default double nextGaussian(double mean, double stddev) {
           if (stddev &lt; 0.0) throw new IllegalArgumentException(&quot;standard deviation must be non-negative&quot;);

           return mean + stddev * RandomSupport.computeNextGaussian(this);
    }
```

